data.description: Situated in a cul de sac within Old Rice Retreat in Cane Bay Plantation, this home offers a blend of comfort and convenience. It boasts 2885 sq ft of living space plus an additional 518 sq ft of unfinished area, ready for personalization.The kitchen is a highlight, with granite countertops, an open layout, and an inviting eat-in space with a built-in desk. The home features a family room, playroom, loft, and sunroom, catering to a variety of activities.Upstairs, the bedrooms provide private sanctuaries, complemented by a conveniently located laundry room. The home is financially appealing with a VA assumable mortgage at 2.25%, and a balance of $187,215.The outdoor area includes a screened-in patio and a large fenced yard with trail access. A fireplace adds a cozy touch.The property is secured with a Brink Security system, active for two more years.  The location is ideal, close to local amenities, including being 1.8 miles from Publix, 1.2 miles from Cane Bay Elementary/Middle School, 2.6 miles from Cane Bay High School, 6.5 miles from Berkeley Preparatory Academy, and 2.7 miles to the YMCA. This home is perfect community living, with resort-style amenities and golf-cart trails throughout the community.
